         <abstract id="aspace_fea4934041ce5ea84cee679d1358ba65">The records consist of correspondence from the business records of William Bostwick (1796-1863), merchant of Augusta, Georgia, and New Haven, Connecticut, who dealt primarily in cotton. While most of the letters are on business, there are personal letters (1854, 1856) from Benjamin Silliman, Noah Porter, James Browning Miles, and Willis Strong Colton. The records also include sixty-two account books.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <corpname identifier="dts_52b92418a09b4312267ecbccf75a80d86907d14f" source="lcsh">
               <part>Bostwick Company</part>
            </corpname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
